WEBVTT

00:06.528 --> 00:08.878
- Previously,
on "Deadly Class"...

00:08.921 --> 00:11.098
- I didn't think it was gonna
feel this way.

00:11.141 --> 00:12.664
- When you were trying
to kiss me?

00:12.708 --> 00:15.537
- Sorry, I didn't mean
to interrupt a quality moment

00:15.580 --> 00:16.799
with you and my boyfriend.

00:18.670 --> 00:20.237
- Kill her!

00:20.281 --> 00:21.543
- You can't hide
from Fiery Jack

00:21.586 --> 00:23.371
and Captain Sensible, Maria!

00:25.242 --> 00:26.765
- Get this crazy bitch off me!

00:26.809 --> 00:28.854
- My son is dead.

00:28.898 --> 00:30.813
You can't understand my pain.

00:30.856 --> 00:32.162
But you will.

00:32.206 --> 00:33.729
- I, too, lost a child.

00:33.772 --> 00:36.253
- If Nahia had lived,
would you have sent her to us?

00:36.297 --> 00:37.341
- I would have been proud

00:37.385 --> 00:38.864
to see her follow
in your footsteps.

00:38.908 --> 00:40.475
- Hello, brother.

00:40.518 --> 00:41.824
You thought you could
hide them?

00:41.867 --> 00:43.304
She'll never be out of danger.

00:43.347 --> 00:45.610
- Marcus, he's the key.

00:45.654 --> 00:48.744
- And why bring this to me
and not Master Lin?

00:48.787 --> 00:51.268
- My pa always told me
to bet on the winning horse.

00:51.312 --> 00:52.835
- Time to suck boot.

00:52.878 --> 00:54.663
I will suck
the most prosperous one.

00:54.706 --> 00:57.448
- Let's put that to the test.

01:01.235 --> 01:04.673
- All right, and one, two,
one, two, three, four.

01:47.759 --> 01:51.850
♪ Oh, kallow, kalay, kalora

01:51.894 --> 01:55.811
♪ A fella he came to me

01:55.854 --> 01:59.641
♪ With legs so orange
and hairy ♪

01:59.684 --> 02:03.384
♪ As big as a tree

02:03.427 --> 02:06.735
♪ A big sweet Sasquatch

02:06.778 --> 02:10.695
♪ With a yam-looking crotch

02:10.739 --> 02:14.569
♪ He's got a stash of weed

02:14.612 --> 02:18.660
♪ And a dream of being free

02:18.703 --> 02:22.533
♪ His name was Shandy

02:22.577 --> 02:25.841
♪ A Shandy, Shandy man

02:25.884 --> 02:29.540
♪ I love him

02:29.584 --> 02:33.849
♪ Oh, Shandy

02:33.892 --> 02:37.244
♪ A Shandy, Shandy man

02:37.287 --> 02:41.335
♪ Oh, kallow, kalay, kalora

02:41.378 --> 02:44.729
all: ♪ That Shandy

02:44.773 --> 02:48.646
♪ Shandy man

02:51.562 --> 02:55.044
- Cousin, that was...

02:55.087 --> 02:56.219
beautiful.

02:56.263 --> 02:57.525
- Yeah.

02:57.568 --> 03:00.484
You have a real gift, sir.

03:00.528 --> 03:02.704
- God smiled on me.

03:09.363 --> 03:11.843
You reek, Mr. Shabnam!

03:11.887 --> 03:15.717
Guess it's time
for some fresh newspaper.

03:15.760 --> 03:17.675
Come on, come on.

03:17.719 --> 03:19.677
There we go.

03:19.721 --> 03:22.854
Thinking about
switching you to diapers

03:22.898 --> 03:25.030
or maybe just...

03:25.074 --> 03:27.816
tie a coffee can
to your hind side.

03:27.859 --> 03:30.297
- It's a jailbreak!

03:33.387 --> 03:36.651
- He's getting away!

03:47.444 --> 03:49.577
- It's over, Johnny.

03:49.620 --> 03:51.405
- Nothing is over.

03:51.448 --> 03:52.667
Nothing!

03:52.710 --> 03:54.799
- This is our First Blood,
Gran Gran!

03:54.843 --> 03:58.586
- My own, special
John Rambo.

04:04.679 --> 04:06.507
Oh, it worked so good!

04:15.472 --> 04:17.996
- You must not love.

04:18.040 --> 04:20.695
You must not marry.

04:20.738 --> 04:23.524
You must discard friends
and ideals.

04:23.567 --> 04:25.439
Violation of these edicts

04:25.482 --> 04:29.356
is the most common downfall
of our kind.

04:29.399 --> 04:32.054
To achieve true commitment
to the life,

04:32.097 --> 04:34.926
we must drown
these frail needs.

04:37.886 --> 04:39.757
- Emotions are
a chemical mirage

04:39.801 --> 04:41.759
that will betray you.

04:41.803 --> 04:44.849
Leave you exposed.

04:50.464 --> 04:52.117
To care for another human

04:52.161 --> 04:56.034
is to create your own
greatest weakness.

04:56.078 --> 05:00.430
If you love someone enough
to die for them...

05:00.474 --> 05:03.651
then you surely will.

05:16.577 --> 05:18.579
- Some speech.

05:18.622 --> 05:20.755
Really got me thinking.

05:20.798 --> 05:22.147
If you're not fighting
for an ideal,

05:22.191 --> 05:24.976
then you're just fighting
for yourself.

05:25.020 --> 05:26.500
If that's what you think,
then that means

05:26.543 --> 05:28.023
everything you said
when I came here

05:28.066 --> 05:30.634
was all garbage, wasn't it?

05:30.678 --> 05:33.681
That pre-rehearsed sermon?

05:33.724 --> 05:35.160
"Give the peasants the power

05:35.204 --> 05:36.597
"to overthrow
their corrupt masters.

05:36.640 --> 05:39.034
"Give my--my rage
a voice loud enough

05:39.077 --> 05:41.515
to be heard around the world."

05:43.430 --> 05:44.953
Jurgen was right.

05:44.996 --> 05:46.737
Carrot on a stick.

05:46.781 --> 05:49.174
You pretend that you empower

05:49.218 --> 05:51.176
the poor outcasts like me,

05:51.220 --> 05:54.484
but you don't care about that.

05:54.528 --> 05:56.007
- The boy who had nothing

05:56.051 --> 05:58.009
is offered the key
to change the world.

05:58.053 --> 06:00.621
Instead of trying, he killed
the man who gave it to him.

06:00.664 --> 06:02.884
- Or another old man exploits
the frustrations

06:02.927 --> 06:05.452
of the next generation
to his own ends.

06:08.977 --> 06:10.848
- The young always
tell themselves

06:10.892 --> 06:14.591
that when they get their chance
they'll do things differently.

06:14.635 --> 06:16.071
Burn it all down.

06:16.114 --> 06:19.117
And yet, all these
millennia later,

06:19.161 --> 06:21.642
the world remains the same.

06:21.685 --> 06:23.731
Humans remain the same.

06:23.774 --> 06:26.429
You either accept it,
navigate it,

06:26.473 --> 06:29.606
or allow yourself
to be suffocated by it.

06:33.523 --> 06:34.742
- From where I'm standing,

06:34.785 --> 06:37.484
you're the one
who's suffocating.

06:37.527 --> 06:39.703
I confessed.

06:39.747 --> 06:42.489
I broke all your rules
and I'm still alive.

06:44.229 --> 06:45.492
You know what I think?

06:45.535 --> 06:48.103
I think once upon a time,

06:48.146 --> 06:50.932
you were on the other side
of this conversation.

06:53.804 --> 06:55.589
I think you let me live

06:55.632 --> 06:58.853
because I'm who you used to be.

06:58.896 --> 07:01.682
I'm who you suffocated.

07:09.733 --> 07:12.127
- Is the boy leaving?

07:15.173 --> 07:18.263
- No.

07:18.307 --> 07:21.615
Everything I'm willing
to die for is right here.

07:38.153 --> 07:39.633
Jesus.

07:39.676 --> 07:41.286
Is that Shabnam's dad?

07:41.330 --> 07:43.811
- His mom could be in there
as well.

07:43.854 --> 07:45.290
- All the more reason
we have to do this now.

07:45.334 --> 07:48.163
- Shabnam's house
is rigged with traps.

07:48.206 --> 07:50.818
Chester has seven to eight
people inside helping him.

07:50.861 --> 07:52.907
- You're sure he has
Chico?

07:52.950 --> 07:55.736
- It's no bluff,
he knows everything.

07:55.779 --> 07:56.824
He has to be
getting information

07:56.867 --> 07:58.042
from someone inside of King's.

07:58.086 --> 07:59.609
- Shabnam's parents.

07:59.653 --> 08:01.655
- There's another problem.

08:01.698 --> 08:03.091
El Diablo.

08:03.134 --> 08:05.833
If this animal
sends him Chico's head,

08:05.876 --> 08:07.269
if he finds out it was me--

08:07.312 --> 08:10.185
- We're gonna need
some serious firepower.

08:10.228 --> 08:12.361
Guns, explosives.

08:12.404 --> 08:15.320
- Y'all must be
out your damn minds.

08:26.157 --> 08:28.290
- Hey!

08:30.161 --> 08:31.946
You know, I didn't mean
to bring this into our lives,

08:31.989 --> 08:33.077
but it's here, and we have--

08:33.121 --> 08:35.123
- We ain't no damn SWAT team!

08:35.166 --> 08:37.038
- No, we're better trained.

08:37.081 --> 08:39.693
It's not just our asses, okay?

08:39.736 --> 08:40.998
Killing Chester?

08:41.042 --> 08:43.131
We'll be saving people, man.

08:43.174 --> 08:45.350
- "There are many causes
I'd die for,

08:45.394 --> 08:47.265
There ain't a single cause
I'd kill for."

08:47.309 --> 08:48.702
- Oh, pacifism.

08:48.745 --> 08:50.007
It's a nice idea,

08:50.051 --> 08:52.227
but if you don't help
once I fight,

08:52.270 --> 08:53.794
then you help
the other side win.

08:53.837 --> 08:57.058
- This hero shit.

08:57.101 --> 08:59.930
It's just a mask you wear
to justify the chaos.

08:59.974 --> 09:02.367
You wanna know what I think?

09:02.411 --> 09:05.893
I think maybe you looking
to get yourself killed.

09:07.721 --> 09:09.810
- Yeah, well,
maybe pretending to be a hero

09:09.853 --> 09:13.640
is better than accepting
that you're not one.

09:13.683 --> 09:15.729
- Gabby's right.

09:15.772 --> 09:18.035
So used to living
in toxic air,

09:18.079 --> 09:21.822
I can't even
see straight anymore.

09:21.865 --> 09:23.040
- What about your friends?

09:23.084 --> 09:24.694
- Shit.

09:24.738 --> 09:28.655
Marcus, if this is what being
your friend gets me...

09:49.937 --> 09:52.374
- Willie's out?

09:55.507 --> 09:58.989
- Okay, the backyard and all
the doors are booby-trapped,

09:59.033 --> 10:02.340
the windows are reinforced,
but if we get some C-4--

10:02.384 --> 10:04.299
- Yeah, yeah, they sell that
at Costco, right?

10:04.342 --> 10:06.301
Next to the big bags
of popcorn.

10:06.344 --> 10:08.216
- There's only one person
I know who can get it.

10:08.259 --> 10:11.001
- Great, let's go.
- No, I said he canget it.

10:11.045 --> 10:12.481
Whether he will
is the real question.

10:12.524 --> 10:15.005
Especially after what
you did to him.

10:16.485 --> 10:17.791
- It's a pass.

10:17.834 --> 10:20.141
- A hard pass.

10:20.184 --> 10:21.708
- If we don't stop Chester

10:21.751 --> 10:23.187
and get Chico's head,
the cartel--

10:23.231 --> 10:24.711
- The cartel will kill her

10:24.754 --> 10:26.321
and the serial killer
will kill you.

10:26.364 --> 10:27.975
Everyone will die.
We get it.

10:28.018 --> 10:29.324
- So why won't you help?

10:29.367 --> 10:31.805
- Help the loony bird
who almost castrated me?

10:31.848 --> 10:33.763
- The hillbillies?
The cartel?

10:33.807 --> 10:36.026
- It's bloody Christmas break.

10:36.070 --> 10:38.463
I've got a plane ticket
and a pint with my name on it.

10:38.507 --> 10:40.770
- We need you.

10:40.814 --> 10:43.207
Please.

10:47.385 --> 10:49.083
- This is the guy
who cut up Marcus?

10:49.126 --> 10:50.432
- No.

10:50.475 --> 10:52.347
Stop letting this madness
into your head, Petra.

10:52.390 --> 10:54.218
Go ruin someone else's holiday.

10:54.262 --> 10:55.263
Shoo.
- All right.

10:55.306 --> 10:56.264
Come on, Saya, let's go.

10:56.307 --> 10:57.918
You were right.
He's all bark.

10:57.961 --> 10:59.180
I thought he wanted to change
the world with a bullet.

10:59.223 --> 11:00.485
- More a figure
of speech, mate.

11:00.529 --> 11:02.792
- Oh.
- Right, so it's all talk.

11:02.836 --> 11:05.229
- You talk a lot about
the good that you want to do

11:05.273 --> 11:07.449
with what you've been
taught here--someday.

11:07.492 --> 11:09.451
- There is no one
who deserves a bullet more

11:09.494 --> 11:11.714
than that monster
we're about to face.

11:11.758 --> 11:14.021
If you are as good
as you say you are,

11:14.064 --> 11:15.892
put your money where
your loud ------- mouth is.

11:15.936 --> 11:18.199
Help us.

11:27.512 --> 11:30.037
- I know a bloke.

11:36.870 --> 11:39.133
- Gao knows.

11:40.874 --> 11:42.527
- How did she find out?

11:42.571 --> 11:45.095
- I don't know.

11:48.925 --> 11:50.231
- What do you think
she will do?

11:50.274 --> 11:54.104
- Father always said
she had shark's teeth.

11:54.148 --> 11:56.933
- Would she--
- Mommy?

11:56.977 --> 12:00.067
What's wrong?

12:00.110 --> 12:02.069
- Everything is fine.

12:02.112 --> 12:05.072
Come here, I need your help
with something.

12:11.992 --> 12:15.604
- And you think she's ready?

12:15.647 --> 12:18.476
- She has been ready
for centuries.

12:18.520 --> 12:21.392
Our bloodline belongs
to the Guild.

12:23.481 --> 12:26.833
You are my firstborn son.

12:26.876 --> 12:29.444
Your destiny is here.

12:29.487 --> 12:31.968
Hers is not.

12:32.012 --> 12:33.796
- I understand, it's just--

12:33.840 --> 12:36.930
- If you understand,
then you understand.

12:36.973 --> 12:39.454
There is nothing more to say.

12:49.507 --> 12:52.510
- I think that China will be
a great adventure for you.

12:58.560 --> 13:01.476
- It is my honor
to have been chosen.

13:06.394 --> 13:10.093
- It belonged
to your grandfather.

13:10.137 --> 13:11.399
- Thank you.

13:11.442 --> 13:13.836
I will take
very good care of it,

13:13.880 --> 13:17.492
and I promise
I will not disappoint you.

13:29.373 --> 13:31.332
- Gao lost her only son

13:31.375 --> 13:33.551
to the temple...

13:33.595 --> 13:35.031
so don't think for a second

13:35.075 --> 13:37.512
she'll allow Nahia
to walk away.

13:37.555 --> 13:40.689
She won't be satisfied
until you've been punished

13:40.732 --> 13:43.648
for not defending her.

13:43.692 --> 13:45.433
Has she reported us
to the Guild?

13:45.476 --> 13:48.915
- No, it would bring shame
to her entire family.

13:50.612 --> 13:51.918
Mostly on her.

13:51.961 --> 13:53.006
- So Gao is the only one

13:53.049 --> 13:55.660
who knows that Nahia
and I are alive?

14:11.633 --> 14:14.331
- Shu.

14:14.375 --> 14:18.118
I'll do what must be done
to protect our family.

14:33.655 --> 14:35.918
- Oh, hey.

14:36.963 --> 14:39.617
- Headed home for Christmas?

14:39.661 --> 14:41.489
Oh, right.

14:41.532 --> 14:45.406
Homeless, no family,
tragic backstory.

14:45.449 --> 14:47.756
We don't really
celebrate Christmas either,

14:47.799 --> 14:50.933
but we're really into
Chinese takeout.

14:55.546 --> 14:58.549
- Hey, Shab, do you...

14:58.593 --> 14:59.855
- Do I what?

14:59.899 --> 15:01.857
- Just, you--you've been
talking to your parents

15:01.901 --> 15:03.728
a lot recently.

15:03.772 --> 15:05.513
- Yeah, yeah.

15:05.556 --> 15:07.645
Normally they're
so preoccupied

15:07.689 --> 15:09.473
with whatever coup
they're funding

15:09.517 --> 15:11.736
that they don't care
that I got an "A" in Forgery--

15:11.780 --> 15:13.695
- It's just, um...

15:13.738 --> 15:16.654
you haven't told them
anything about me, right?

15:16.698 --> 15:18.134
- Pardon?

15:18.178 --> 15:20.658
- Get out.

15:20.702 --> 15:22.008
- Oh, so you're not even trying

15:22.051 --> 15:25.054
to keep this thing
a secret anymore.

15:38.546 --> 15:40.374
- So what did Lex say?

15:40.417 --> 15:42.854
- He'll help.
Petra, too.

15:49.035 --> 15:51.907
- I keep waiting
for you to apologize.

15:51.951 --> 15:53.996
Some sort of acknowledgement

15:54.040 --> 15:57.826
of this huge secret you kept.

15:57.869 --> 16:01.438
- I'm sorry, I just--
I thought...

16:01.482 --> 16:02.962
I--I wasn't sure
you could handle it.

16:03.005 --> 16:04.267
- And Saya could?

16:04.311 --> 16:07.749
- She knew about
the Boys' Home already, so I...

16:07.792 --> 16:10.665
Shit.

16:12.710 --> 16:14.625
- I don't care.

16:14.669 --> 16:16.540
I trust you.

16:16.584 --> 16:20.718
I can't add worrying about this
to the list.

16:20.762 --> 16:23.460
I just...

16:27.073 --> 16:29.640
I don't want
to be alone tonight.

16:31.077 --> 16:33.862
Stay with me?

16:33.905 --> 16:36.734
It could be our last time.

16:36.778 --> 16:38.954
- Of course.

16:56.145 --> 16:59.627
- Alcoholics call it
"doing a geographic."

17:01.542 --> 17:03.109
Doesn't matter how far you go.

17:03.152 --> 17:06.590
Your problems will follow you.

17:06.634 --> 17:09.767
- My moms used to call me
"Peter Pan."

17:09.811 --> 17:12.074
Said I'd never grow up.

17:12.118 --> 17:15.077
She sent me here
to change all that.

17:16.296 --> 17:20.691
But if this
is what growing up means,

17:20.735 --> 17:22.258
you can count me out.

17:22.302 --> 17:24.956
- But leaving now
when we're in so much trouble?

17:25.000 --> 17:28.569
After what Marcus did for you?

17:43.236 --> 17:46.978
- Okay, yeah.

17:47.022 --> 17:50.156
When he first hit that dude...

17:50.199 --> 17:53.159
he saved my ass.

17:55.552 --> 17:57.902
But that second hit...

18:02.646 --> 18:05.867
He didn't kill that dude
for me.

18:08.609 --> 18:12.134
It's this place.

18:12.178 --> 18:15.050
This place is changing him.

18:17.705 --> 18:19.881
It's changing all of y'all.

18:28.324 --> 18:31.022
- We love you, Willie.

18:31.066 --> 18:34.156
This is your home.

18:34.200 --> 18:36.202
But if you leave now,

18:36.245 --> 18:38.682
you will regret it
for the rest of your life.

18:38.726 --> 18:40.684
- Maybe.

18:42.904 --> 18:45.689
But if I know one thing
about Peter Pan...

18:47.648 --> 18:50.172
He can't become a pirate.

18:58.398 --> 19:00.139
- Meeting Lex's contact

19:00.182 --> 19:01.879
at The Adolescents show
tonight.

19:01.923 --> 19:04.882
Bring whatever money
you've got.

19:04.926 --> 19:08.843
- I, uh--look, have Lex
store the explosives

19:08.886 --> 19:10.105
in the back of the comic shop.

19:10.149 --> 19:12.151
I'll open the store tomorrow.

19:12.194 --> 19:14.065
No one else be there.
- You're not coming?

19:14.109 --> 19:15.284
You're just leaving me
to deal with it?

19:15.328 --> 19:17.895
- I--I promised Maria.

19:17.939 --> 19:19.158
She's upset.

19:19.201 --> 19:20.594
- Well, you know what,
do whatever you gotta do

19:20.637 --> 19:21.595
to straighten her out, Romeo.

19:21.638 --> 19:23.074
We need her
in full form tomorrow.

19:23.118 --> 19:26.121
- Hey, listen, I never
thanked you for all the help.

19:26.165 --> 19:28.167
- Don't flatter yourself.

19:28.210 --> 19:30.734
No choice.
You're my pledge.

19:32.736 --> 19:34.390
But if you get everyone
killed tomorrow

19:34.434 --> 19:35.435
and you screw it up,

19:35.478 --> 19:37.785
I'm the one
stuck paying the price.

20:02.636 --> 20:05.073
- Probably not all
mall Santas are pedophiles,

20:05.116 --> 20:07.467
but, I mean, the percentages
have gotta be high, right?

20:07.510 --> 20:09.295
- Well, now I'm thinking on it,
Christmas is that

20:09.338 --> 20:10.774
one night a year where
a strange bearded man

20:10.818 --> 20:12.167
is allowed
to sneak into the house.

20:12.211 --> 20:13.299
- ♪ Dashing through the snow

20:13.342 --> 20:16.215
♪ In a one-horse
open sleigh ♪

20:16.258 --> 20:18.826
♪ Over the fields we go,
Laughing all the way, ha-- ♪

20:20.436 --> 20:23.352
- God, you are kidding me.

20:25.572 --> 20:29.402
His master, the piety king
of lecture town sent you solo?

20:29.445 --> 20:32.753
- He's dealing with
another mess.

20:32.796 --> 20:34.363
Why'd you pick the show?

20:34.407 --> 20:35.625
- I already had tickets

20:35.669 --> 20:37.627
and I was not gonna miss
The Adolescents.

